FBIS3-32752 "drlat030_o_94010" FBIS-LAT-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Colombia Gaviria `Played Down' U.S. Military Presence Issue PA1202022194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 12 Feb 94 PA1202022194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Azucena Lievano, from the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] We have learned that President Cesar Gaviria made the defense minister responsible for responding to the State Council's concern about the presence of U.S. military engineers in Juanchaco. It has been said that the president has played down the issue, and that he let a colonel, who is also an attorney, draft the response letter. What happened to the people who advise the president on issues as delicate as this one?
